# DR Lookup

Queries Oracle for Discrepancy Reports (DRs) filtered by module name, lookback window, and a maximum row cap. Returns results as a `pandas.DataFrame`.

Follows the same `OracleBaseDatabaseModule` pattern used throughout the project ‚Äî the connection layer, `.env` keys, column naming, and query ordering are all consistent with `wo_database.py`.

---

## Requirements

```bash
pip install oracledb pandas python-dotenv
```

---

## Configuration

Uses the same `.env` file as the rest of the project. No new keys are required.

| Key | Description |
|---|---|
| `ORACLE_HOST` | Oracle server hostname |
| `ORACLE_SERVICE_NAME` | Oracle service name |
| `ORACLE_USER` | Oracle username |
| `ORACLE_PASSWORD` | Oracle password |
| `ORACLE_PORT` | Oracle port ‚Äî defaults to `1521` if not set |

---

## Setup

Before running, set the actual Oracle table/view name at the top of `dr_lookup.py`:

```python
_DR_TABLE = "YOUR_SCHEMA.YOUR_DR_TABLE"
```

This should be the same table used in `wo_database.py`.

