## Usage

### As a module (imported)

```python
from oracle.dr_lookup import DRLookup
from oracle.driver.oracle_connection import OracleConnectionConfig

config = OracleConnectionConfig(
    host="your-host",
    service_name="your-service",
    username="your-user",
    password="your-password",
)

with DRLookup(config) as db:
    df = db.get_drs_by_module(
        module_name="MODULE_NAME",
        days_back=30,
        max_results=500,
    )

print(df)
```

### From the command line (standalone)

```bash
python dr_lookup.py --module "MODULE_NAME" --days 30 --max 500
```

| Argument | Required | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `--module` | Yes | ‚Äî | Exact module name to filter on |
| `--days` | No | `30` | Number of calendar days to look back |
| `--max` | No | `1000` | Hard cap on rows returned |

