## Columns Returned

All column names are lowercased, consistent with the rest of the project.

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `order_no` | str | Work order number |
| `order_type` | str / None | |
| `order_start_date` | datetime / None | Lookback filter applied to this column |
| `order_end_date` | datetime / None | |
| `part_no` | str | |
| `module_description` | str / None | |
| `module_name` | str / None | Filter column |
| `module_assy_level` | str / None | |
| `program` | str / None | May contain embedded module name ‚Äî clean at call site if needed |
| `module_serial_num` | str / None | |
| `dr_id` | str | Primary unique identifier for a DR |
| `dr_title` | str / None | |
| `dr_type` | str / None | |
| `dr_defect_code` | str / None | |
| `dr_notes` | str / None | |
| `dr_text_timestamp` | datetime / None | |
| `dr_text_1` | str / None | Free-text field |
| `dr_text_2` | str / None | Free-text field |
| `dr_text_3` | str / None | Free-text field |
| `dr_text_4` | str / None | Free-text field |
| `dr_text_5` | str / None | Free-text field |

Date columns (`order_start_date`, `order_end_date`, `dr_text_timestamp`) are coerced to `pd.Timestamp` / `NaT` automatically.

---

## Query Behaviour

- Lookback filter: `order_start_date >= SYSDATE - days_back`
- Row cap: `FETCH FIRST n ROWS ONLY` applied at the database level ‚Äî not in Python
- Result ordering: `module_name, part_no, order_no, dr_id, dr_text_timestamp`
- Multiple rows may share a `dr_id` ‚Äî each represents a timestamped text entry for the same DR, consistent with how `wo_database.py` and the pipeline handle grouping

